===Etymology===
From the Greek ''[[esoteros]]'', meaning ''inner'', ''esoteric'' originally referred to the secret (vs public) teachings of Greek philosophers.

===Adjective===
'''esoteric'''

# Having to do with concepts that are highly theoretical and without obvious practical application.
# Understood only by a chosen few or an inner circle.
# Confidential; private.

